channel.title: [PI] Cache Help
channel.description:
Hey everyone,
I am looking for a updated version of "Toms cache editor". Sadly the version i have at the moment is outdated and will not load my cache it just freezes. I have searched for a little while and cannot find a updated one mabey because there is not one or i just suck at searching :L
If anyone here has a updated version or some similar program i would be extremely greatful if i could get a link
*EDIT* I decided to run the Jar with CMD and i kept getting this error;
[code] Badseek - pos:(random number) len:97539058[/code] I did some further investigating and i believe that the problem is my cache size, the "main_file_cache" is too big, is there anyway to compress it down?
Many Thanks
LunaRSPS

item.title: [PI] Cache Help
item.dc:creator: @Tutorial Tutorial
item.description:
@Tutorial wrote:

Unfortunately, the only way you can edit/remove things from the cache is if you can actually access it with a cache suite. I believe someone released a cache editor that could load bigger caches, but I’m not quite sure where because I can not find the link to it at the moment.
